solution: ```class RecentCounter {
    private final java.util.Deque<Integer> q = new java.util.ArrayDeque<>();

    public RecentCounter() {
    }

    public int ping(int t) {
        q.addLast(t);
        while (q.peekFirst() < t - 3000) {
            q.removeFirst();
        }
        return q.size();
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(1) amortized per ping
space complexity: O(n) where n is the number of pings in the sliding window (≤ 3000)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses a FIFO queue to store only the pings within the last 3000 ms. Each ping is added once and removed at most once, giving amortized O(1) time. Space is bounded by the 3000 ms window size.

